I love you Matt. But it's pretty clear you seem to have no knowledge about the offroad features of this vehical and trucks in general. 1. It has a lockable rear diff not a limited slip. HUUGE difference. 2. The leaf springs are a better suspension in this application for towing and high loads and offroading 3. The ladder chassis is much better for offroading. 4
The base trim is a fleet vehical so talking about things not being standard is a misnomer. It's meant to be cheap transportation and capability for companies. 5. The diesel is the third from the top engine option terms of power and acceleration. Not the bottom. It makes a lot of torque which is really what a truck is all about.
